description: This table holds data for the specific embryos transferred during a cycle.

columns.name: RECORD_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier for the cycle record.

columns.name: LINE
columns.description: The line number for the information associated with this record. Multiple pieces of information can be associated with this record.

columns.name: EMBRYO_STAGE_C_NAME
columns.description:
Stores stage at transfer for a specific embryo.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 Category Entries: 


1 Cell


2 Cell


3 Cell


4 Cell


5 Cell


6 Cell


7 Cell


8 Cell


More than 8


Morula


Early Blastocyst


Blastocyst


Full Blastocyst


Expanded Blastocyst


Hatching Blastocyst


Hatched Blastocyst


Unknown

columns.name: EMBRYO_GRADE_C_NAME
columns.description:
Stores grade at transfer for a specific embryo.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 Category Entries: 


Good


Fair


Poor

columns.name: EMBRYO_FERT_METHOD_C_NAME
columns.description:
Stores the embryo's fertilization type at a given transfer.


May contain organization-specific values: No


 Category Entries: 


In Vitro Fertilization


In-Vitro Fertilization with Intra-Cytoplasmic Sperm Injection


Intracytoplasmic Sperm Injection


Conventional IVF


Intrauterine Insemination


Timed Intercourse


Therapeutic Donor Insemination


None

columns.name: EMBRYO_ASSISTED_HATCHING_YN
columns.description:
Stores whether this specific embryo had any hatching assistance.


May contain organization-specific values: No


 Category Entries: 


No


Yes

columns.name: EGG_EMBRYO_GAMETE_SOURCE_C_NAME
columns.description:
Stores the source of the egg for a specific embryo.  The source being the participant that the gamete came from (donor, partner, self, etc).


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 Category Entries: 


Autologous


Partner


Known Donor


Anonymous Donor


Mixed


Embryo Donor


Oocyte Contributor and Intended Parent

columns.name: SPERM_EMBRYO_GAMETE_SOURCE_C_NAME
columns.description:
Stores the sperm source for a specific embryo.  The source being the participant that the gamete came from (donor, partner, etc).


 The category values for this column were already listed for column: EGG_EMBRYO_GAMETE_SOURCE_C_NAME

columns.name: EGG_EMBRYO_GAMETE_STATE_C_NAME
columns.description:
Stores the state of the egg at the beginning of the cycle.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 Category Entries: 


Fresh


Thawed


Frozen Embryo


Not Applicable

columns.name: SPERM_EMBRYO_GAMETE_STATE_C_NAME
columns.description:
Stores the state of the sperm at the beginning of the cycle.


 The category values for this column were already listed for column: EGG_EMBRYO_GAMETE_STATE_C_NAME

columns.name: EMBRYO_COMMENTS
columns.description: Stores the comments for a specific embryo at transfer.

columns.name: EMBRYO_TRANSFER_DAY
columns.description: Stores the transfer day of a specific embryo.

columns.name: EMBRYO_OVERRIDE
columns.description: Stores an embryo ID that a user specified. If not set, an embryo ID based on the line number (such as "Embryo 1") is shown to the end user.

columns.name: EMBRYO_PGT_A_C_NAME
columns.description:
Stores the documentation for a specific embryo's PGT-A testing during an embryo transfer.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 Category Entries: 


Euploid


Aneuploid


Not Tested


No Result


Pending


Mosaic, High Level


Mosaic, Low Level


Inconclusive

columns.name: EMBRYO_PGT_M_C_NAME
columns.description:
Stores the documentation for a specific embryo's PGT-M testing during an embryo transfer.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 Category Entries: 


Not Tested


No Result


Pending


Affected


Unaffected


Carrier


Multiple


At Risk


Low Risk


No Risk


Inconclusive

columns.name: EMBRYO_PGT_SR_C_NAME
columns.description:
Stores the documentation for a specific embryo's PGT-SR testing during an embryo transfer.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 Category Entries: 


Not Tested


No Result


Pending


Affected


Unaffected


Balanced


Unbalanced


Inconclusive

columns.name: SPECIFIC_EMBRYO_GAMETE_STATE_C_NAME
columns.description:
Stores the state of the embryo (thawed or fresh) at the beginning of the cycle. Thawed means the embryo was thawed as an embryo. Fresh means that either the egg and sperm are fresh, or they were thawed as gametes and then fertilized.


 The category values for this column were already listed for column: EGG_EMBRYO_GAMETE_STATE_C_NAME

columns.name: EMBRYO_DONATED_YN
columns.description:
Stores whether the embryo was donated for an embryo transfer cycle.


 The category values for this column were already listed for column: EMBRYO_ASSISTED_HATCHING_YN
